### buildODRType() {#accca8844cacd32b33a52a9c1ddf3876c}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>DICompositeType &#42; DICompositeType::buildODRType (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/llvmcontext">LLVMContext</a> &amp; Context, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mdstring">MDString</a> &amp; Identifier, unsigned Tag, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mdstring">MDString</a> &#42; Name, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/metadata">Metadata</a> &#42; File, unsigned Line, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/metadata">Metadata</a> &#42; Scope, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/metadata">Metadata</a> &#42; BaseType, uint64&#95;t SizeInBits, uint32&#95;t AlignInBits, uint64&#95;t OffsetInBits, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/metadata">Metadata</a> &#42; Specification, uint32&#95;t NumExtraInhabitants, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/dinode/#aded082f50ef7ec8cbcd27f2b0dec28a9">DIFlags</a> Flags, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/metadata">Metadata</a> &#42; Elements, unsigned RuntimeLang, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/metadata">Metadata</a> &#42; VTableHolder, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/metadata">Metadata</a> &#42; TemplateParams, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/metadata">Metadata</a> &#42; Discriminator, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/metadata">Metadata</a> &#42; DataLocation, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/metadata">Metadata</a> &#42; Associated, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/metadata">Metadata</a> &#42; Allocated, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/metadata">Metadata</a> &#42; Rank, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/metadata">Metadata</a> &#42; Annotations)</>}
  labels = {["static"]}>
Build a <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/dicompositetype">DICompositeType</a> with the given ODR identifier.

Looks up the mapped <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/dicompositetype">DICompositeType</a> for the given ODR <code>Identifier</code>. If it doesn&#39;t exist, creates a new one. If it does exist and <em><a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/ditype/#a78039d632c4d3f50030540598ba03b47">isForwardDecl()</a></em>, and the new arguments would be a definition, mutates the the type in place. In either case, returns the type.

If not <em><a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/llvmcontext/#a89d7bf0d39222f8aba5ebf358076ce50">LLVMContext::isODRUniquingDebugTypes()</a></em>, this function returns nullptr.
